<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="54.[171,1379,3161,3474]" pageId="54" pageNumber="112">
The form nesea named by K. Andersen in 1909 from western and central 
<collectingCountry name="Solomon Islands" pageId="54" pageNumber="112">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
has been synonymized with nominate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1909" box="[817,908,3275,3308]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Dobsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="112" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="inermis">inermis</taxonomicName>
by most authors, which thisis followed here. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
